            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favors &amp; several inclosures are before me. I
                    want no minutiae or secret history of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> hospitals.
                    The public only expect general accounts. I see in the list of the Books I sent
                    to be distributed, another omission of <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Whites</persName> for besides forgetting to send a <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0008">first vol.</title></bibl> to <persName ref="pe0103">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Golborne</persName>, another was omitted
                    to <persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Jackson</persName>, which you will
                    please to tell him of. Is the <placeName ref="pl1041">new episcopal chapel</placeName>
                    finished? Pray forward the inclosed as soon as possible. I mourn for a very
                    worthy <persName ref="pe0812">mother in Law</persName>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute><signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho.
                            Pennant</persName></signed>.
                <dateline>March 24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>I have made full use of <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0158">Keithâ€™s
                                Bishops</title></bibl> ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> the abbies in
                        <placeName ref="pl0316">Dundee</placeName>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
